KwaZulu-Natal club AmaZulu has extended the contracts of veteran strikers Mabhuti Khanyeza (36) and Siyabonga Nomvete (40) by a further year and they will remain at the club until the end of 2019. JOHANNESBURG - KwaZulu-Natal club AmaZulu has extended the contracts of veteran strikers Mabhuti Khanyeza (36) and Siyabonga Nomvete (40) by a further year and they will remain at the club until the end of 2019. Both Khanyeza and Nomvete are the only players still active that have scored more than 100 career goals in the Premier Soccer League. Their contracts expired at the end of June, but the club has decided to retain their services for another season. Along with Khanyeza and Nomvete, former Kaizer Chiefs striker Camaldine Abraw has also been re-signed by the club on a one-year deal after his initial six-month contract had expired.